benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId} - Transfer a bundle to another account

covered: Valid payload flows (201 Created) including minimal and full payloads (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05, TC26).
Comprehensive error handling and input validation testing (400/404/401/503/500) across multiple scenarios (TC07, TC08-12, TC13, TC14, TC24).
Authorization and authentication scenarios tested (missing header and unauthorized token) (TC11, TC13).
State variation coverage (empty database and partially populated database) (TC22, TC23).
Edge cases coverage (empty pluginProperty, extra parameters, max header lengths, large payload) (TC18, TC19, TC20, TC21).
Performance coverage (TC27-30) including response time and concurrency, plus TC30 on resource utilization.
Security coverage (SQL injection in accountId, XSS in pluginProperty) (TC15, TC16).
gaps: Rate limiting / throttling behavior not tested.
Caching behavior headers (ETag, Cache-Control) and cache validation not tested.
Explicit 403 Forbidden test for insufficient permissions not covered.
recommendations: Add a dedicated duplicate submission test to validate idempotency and handling of repeated POSTs.
Introduce rate limiting tests and checks for proper throttling under load.
Add tests asserting caching headers and proper caching behavior where applicable (ETag/Cache-Control).
Add a 403 Forbidden scenario to ensure proper handling of insufficient permissions.
Consider broader boundary tests for additional edge cases and long-term robustness (e.g., longer pluginProperty arrays, more complex nested structures).
